That’s a wrap on season 2 of #GrandCrew! So grateful I got to play with these beautiful humans again. Premiering spring 2023 on @nbc and @peacocktv!

Moving out of my apartment of two years yesterday felt like the perfect way to end the year. One chapter is closing while another one begins. My life has had the craziest ups and downs since 2021 and they all happened right here. So here’s to learning from the past and embracing new beginnings! I’m ready for you 2023! 23 is my favorite number, so it has to be great. Wishing you and yours an incredible year. Let’s go! #2023 #happynewyear

Okay here we go…the kitchen reveal! Swipe for before/after pics and my inspiration board. Green is one of my favorite colors and I wanted a clean looking kitchen with deep green matte tiling and brass details. I got just that thanks to my designer @sol_designbuild and her team. Appliances are important and I wanted a sleek fridge and range to complete the look. That’s where @forteappliances comes in! Beautifully designed stainless steel appliances with impeccable details like the brass bezels on the range. The fridge is tall but thin and the depth was short enough to not block my pretty windows yet deep enough to hold all my essentials and more. I went with a range hood instead of an OTR microwave because your girl is cooking more and needs that exhaust system. I love my new kitchen!!! More remodeling pics to come. #homedecor #remodeling #kitchenremodel #kitchendesign #forteappliances

Photos by @sylvia.wakana

LA : help me out…looking for someone who can get my hair this straight without a flatiron. This is NY Dominican hair salon straight. Does it exist in LA? I know one place but looking for others when I can’t get in there. Any and all leads would be greatly appreciated. 🙏🏽 PS - I’m happier than I look in this photo. Just look at the hair. 🥴😂

Because this kitchen remodel deserves its own reel too 🥰 So in love with how it turned out. Wanted to share which products I got from @forteappliances because y’all got questions! The range is its 30” gas range with brass bezels. The brass bezels really pulled together the look of the kitchen and compliment the brass hardware through out the kitchen. For the fridge, I went with their 30” built-in, bottom freezer refrigerator because it was slim enough to fit where it is without blocking my window or porch door but still large enough to fit all my needs. Plus it has an ice maker and water dispenser. I’ve been using them both for 3 weeks now and I’m in love! I’m actually excited to cook! So YES, I highly recommend Forté Appliances. I also highly recommend you hire my designer @sol_designbuild, because really she’s the best and did all the work. #blessed

🚨Spoiler Alert🚨 In case you haven’t seen last night’s episode of #GrandCrew. Also what are you waiting for?! Go stream that sh*t on @peacock!

But if you have, then you know it was Fay’s last episode of the season and she does, in fact, move back to NY. Thank you so much for all the love, tweets & DMs. They’ve been amazing to read. 🥹♥️

Whether or not there’s a season 3 or Fay ever returns to LA is currently unknown but regardless of what happens in the future, all I can do is be extremely grateful for this journey. Thank you @philaugustaj, Dan Goor, Susie Farris, @universaltv, @nbc, & @peacock for the opportunity to be part of the crew.

Thank you to my cast mates for always having my back and quickly becoming my family on and off the screen. Love y’all.

And thank you to the @grandcwriters and the entire crew who worked tirelessly to bring this magic to the screen.

Forever grateful for all of you. #clangclang

I’m not in LA this week but I am in NY next week and plan to picket there in my hometown. I hope this strike doesn’t last long but it’s so damn necessary. I’ve been a member of the WGA since 2019 and a member of SAG since 2005. Unions are important! Especially when giant corporations refuse to respect creatives while continuing to profit off of their art! Thank you to everyone out there today and every day moving forward. ✊🏽 #WGAstrong #WGAonstrike
Proud of my unions. Proud of my city. #wgastrong #sagaftra #dothewritething #grandcrew #severance

SUNDIALED : Ann Arbor, MI
In the past five years, I’ve been a part of about 10 or so short films as a writer, director, producer, actor or some combination of all four because I absolutely love it. There’s something really special about getting a group of talented people together to create something for no other reason than the love of storytelling. But making SUNDIALED in Ann Arbor, the hometown of the writer/director/lead @gfgoss and his co-lead sis @alyssanena was truly magical. To see a community come together to support their friend make his first film had me 🥹. Can’t wait until we get to share this special film with you. And PS - this cast and crew was incredible! #comingsoon @sundialedshort

It's the first time the #WGA and #SAGAFTRA have gone on strike at the same time since 1960 -- so it’s only right we check in with writers and actors to see how they’re doing in the midst of making history. ✊🏾

We caught up with actress, writer & filmmaker @grasiemercedes to discuss the demands of the creatives on the frontlines and the impact of the strike on the entertainment industry.

If you’re a member of the #WGA or #SAGAFTRA, click the link in bio to get a FREE ticket to CultureCon NYC. 🎟

Last night was pure magic. An evening two years in the making that reminded me and everyone in that room why art is so important. A reminder desperately needed at a time like this. Every single person involved in the evening from the cast to the crew, musicians and clinicians gave their soul and left their hearts on that stage and in that screen. THIS is what it’s all about. @iammattlaw I am so grateful to have your artistry and friendship in my life. You inspire me daily with your genius. To the cast of TRUE, y’all are so damn talented you make me want to be better and I can’t wait to work with each of you again. Last night was just the beginning. THIS IS SPECIAL. I’m a sappy mess right now so I’ll end with this…we all deserve to be seen, we all deserve love, we all deserve therapy. “Vulnerability is the privilege of our generation.” Thank you to everyone who came out last night, your energy was exhilarating. #TRUE

CHIMERA. A weekend of indie filmmaking lead by Afro-Latina @kryzzgautier and her all female (+ @brettlmarshall) crew. Sci-fi, future, lovely fun. And I got to play with my talented buddy @christopher__rivas and new friends @thejessadams & @julianaaidenmartinez Grateful to still be able to partake in creativity while on strike. #chimera BTS photos by @sarahkcphotos

I was a 90s teen and have always loved fashion so when I was invited to check out the @esprit pop-up at The Grove I got very excited. The shop did not disappoint! First of all, it’s beautiful and blasts the best 80s/90s playlist of all time. Second, and probably most importantly, the clothes are so good! Men's and women's pieces that highlight the best of ESPRIT’s designs from denim and knits to tops featuring the classic logo. But some my favorite pieces were the vintage tees and jeans they sell only in-store! So, if you’re in LA, head over to The Grove ASAP and check it out. The pop up will be there until the end of the year and you don’t wanna miss it! #esprit #shotonfilm

social_posts.post_text: I don’t think I’ll ever have the words to truly express what being a part of @trueimmersive has meant for me. The healing it has provided, the family it has formed and the creativity and inspiration it has garnered is simply indescribable. Last night marked our 5th sold out show in Los Angeles and while they’ve all been amazing, somehow each one is more magical and alive than the last. And the best part is…I think we’re just getting started. I love every single person involved in this project and I thank every single person who has come out to support us. Until next year! 🙏🏽♥️ #TRUE
